00:24:15.040 --> 00:24:17.720
emperor would go to war
without first having

00:24:17.720 --> 00:24:22.430
a careful augury done to make
sure that the birds said it was

00:24:22.430 --> 00:24:24.650
an auspicious-- by the way
the word auspicious comes

00:24:24.650 --> 00:24:27.210
from augery-- time to go to war.

00:24:27.210 --> 00:24:30.990
So that kind of system has
been used for a long time.

00:24:30.990 --> 00:24:33.240
Now here's the
interesting thing.

00:24:33.240 --> 00:24:36.210
I didn't know this till
I started the course.

00:24:36.210 --> 00:24:39.560
Well, today if we
make a prediction,

00:24:39.560 --> 00:24:41.570
we check if we were
right, or at least we

00:24:41.570 --> 00:24:44.380
do the best we can to
check if we were right.

00:24:44.380 --> 00:24:48.960
Aristotle, who was the greatest
scientist who ever lived up--

00:24:48.960 --> 00:24:52.694
according to Islamic
scientists, Renaissance

00:24:52.694 --> 00:24:53.610
scientists, et cetera.

00:24:53.610 --> 00:24:57.690
So for like 1,000 years
plus after he lived,

00:24:57.690 --> 00:25:02.970
he was the definitive
reference source.

00:25:02.970 --> 00:25:05.440
And he believed that you
could reason things out.

00:25:05.440 --> 00:25:07.630
And so that if a prediction,
if a predictive system,

00:25:07.630 --> 00:25:10.260
seemed right, it was right.

00:25:10.260 --> 00:25:12.210
You didn't really have to check.

00:25:12.210 --> 00:25:15.390
He did involve-- his
systems involved data,

00:25:15.390 --> 00:25:19.730
they just didn't involve going
back and adjusting very much.

00:25:19.730 --> 00:25:22.020
It was more about the
beauty of the prediction.

00:25:22.020 --> 00:25:24.550
So as I mentioned before,
the Islamic scientists

00:25:24.550 --> 00:25:26.640
looked to Aristotle
as their hero.

00:25:26.640 --> 00:25:30.210
But after a few hundred years
of translating Greek to Arabic,

00:25:30.210 --> 00:25:32.840
they decided that they
didn't necessarily

00:25:32.840 --> 00:25:34.830
agree with everything
that he said.

00:25:34.830 --> 00:25:37.420
And from my own
research, not necessarily

00:25:37.420 --> 00:25:39.640
that all historians of
science would agree with this,

00:25:39.640 --> 00:25:42.530
it seems to me that a lot
of the traditions that we've

00:25:42.530 --> 00:25:44.470
follow today in
terms of measuring

00:25:44.470 --> 00:25:46.330
the accuracy of a
prediction really

00:25:46.330 --> 00:25:52.440
came from the 800 to 1,200
AD period of this heyday

00:25:52.440 --> 00:25:54.280
of Islamic science.

00:25:54.280 --> 00:25:56.170
And so, once you make
those measurements,

00:25:56.170 --> 00:25:58.480
then you can start
improving your system.

00:25:58.480 --> 00:26:01.650
And it does, unfortunately,
lead to things like epicycles

00:26:01.650 --> 00:26:04.990
upon epicycles, and weird ideas
about how the solar system

00:26:04.990 --> 00:26:07.950
works that do work but
it's not physically

00:26:07.950 --> 00:26:09.280
how the solar system works.

00:26:09.280 --> 00:26:11.910
And we'll come back to
that in a little while.

00:26:11.910 --> 00:26:14.620
But anyway, then you wind up
with this kind of feedback loop

00:26:14.620 --> 00:26:17.460
where you can keep taking more
data, checking out your system,

00:26:17.460 --> 00:26:19.220
maybe adding something to it.

